436
00:22:03,090 --> 00:22:04,020
What did you say?

437
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:06,260
I was just joking with you.

438
00:22:08,370 --> 00:22:09,700
Don't mind me. Please have a seat.

439
00:22:14,130 --> 00:22:15,980
I love to joke around.

440
00:22:16,740 --> 00:22:17,220
By the way,

441
00:22:18,020 --> 00:22:19,260
what's with the scholarly getup

442
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:21,660
after returning to the capital?

443
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:24,260
I returned to my hometown
to visit my family

444
00:22:24,260 --> 00:22:25,370
after the war.

445
00:22:25,660 --> 00:22:27,330
That's why I dressed myself as such.

446
00:22:27,570 --> 00:22:28,500
What else will you be doing

447
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:29,460
besides visiting your family?

448
00:22:31,900 --> 00:22:33,740
I have official affairs
to handle in the capital this time around.

449
00:22:34,090 --> 00:22:36,130
Actually, it's considered
my private matter.

450
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:36,850
Your private matter?

451
00:22:37,940 --> 00:22:39,500
Is it interesting?

452
00:22:40,020 --> 00:22:42,020
It's a long story.

453
00:22:42,900 --> 00:22:44,980
Before this, General Yuan Buqu

454
00:22:44,980 --> 00:22:46,130
was struck by a poison arrow

455
00:22:46,290 --> 00:22:47,900
during the war.

456
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,980
His life was in danger.

457
00:22:51,220 --> 00:22:52,260
Luckily, my master taught me

458
00:22:52,260 --> 00:22:54,130
a secret technique
that could neutralize poison.

459
00:22:54,500 --> 00:22:56,130
That's how he was able to survive.

460
00:22:57,610 --> 00:22:59,700
However, he hasn't recovered completely.

461
00:22:59,700 --> 00:23:00,740
And he didn't heed my advice.

462
00:23:01,020 --> 00:23:02,260
He returned to the battlefield
and fought our enemies.

463
00:23:02,770 --> 00:23:05,370
That's why it has left a mark on his body.

464
00:23:05,660 --> 00:23:06,570
What will happen then?

465
00:23:07,260 --> 00:23:08,130
He will suffer a relapse

466
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:09,090
after 100 days.

467
00:23:11,660 --> 00:23:12,660
Pingwei, is that true?

468
00:23:15,770 --> 00:23:16,500
That's right.

469
00:23:17,420 --> 00:23:19,660
Buqu is a reckless person.

470
00:23:19,940 --> 00:23:21,740
That's why he landed himself in trouble.

471
00:23:24,090 --> 00:23:24,980
And, Your Highness,

472
00:23:25,330 --> 00:23:26,900
once he suffers a relapse,

473
00:23:27,130 --> 00:23:28,330
even Hua Tuo [*A legendary surgeon]

474
00:23:28,660 --> 00:23:29,850
won't be able to save him.

475
00:23:32,330 --> 00:23:33,370
I was suddenly reminded of this issue

476
00:23:33,370 --> 00:23:34,660
when I was in my hometown.

477
00:23:35,020 --> 00:23:36,740
That's why I came to the capital

478
00:23:36,940 --> 00:23:38,090
in search of the general.

479
00:23:39,370 --> 00:23:40,740
The general will be fine

480
00:23:40,740 --> 00:23:41,700
